'''Steve Nkanu Kapuadi''' (born 30 April 1998) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for Polish club [[Widzew Łódź]]. Born in France, he represents the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo national team]].

==Club career==
After passing through the Le Mans training center up to U17 level, he left his hometown club for Angers, before joining the [[Zulte Waregem]] training center in Belgium. He then moved to La Gantoise, where he joined the club's reserve team. Kapuadi moved to [[AS Trenčín]] from partner club of [[Inter Bratislava]] during the winter of 2020. He made his professional [[Slovak Super Liga|Fortuna Liga]] debut for Trenčín during a home fixture, at their temporary home ground at [[Štadión pod Dubňom|pod Dubňom]], against [[MFK Zemplín Michalovce|Zemplín Michalovce]] on 15 February 2020. He played the entire 90 minutes of the match as a [[centre back]], along with another winter arrival [[Richard Križan]]. Trenčín went on to defeat Zemplín with a 8:1 victory.<ref>[https://ulk.futbalnet.sk/zapas/426437/ AS Trencin - MFK Zemplín Michalovce] 15 February 2020, futbalnet.sk</ref> Kapuadi also made three further appearances in the remaining games of the regular season, becoming a regular in the starting eleven.

On 2 June 2022, Kapuadi was announced as Polish [[Ekstraklasa]] side [[Wisła Płock]]'s new signing, penning a one-and-a-half-year deal, with an extension option until June 2025.<ref>{{cite web |title=Steve Kapuadi trzecim nowym zawodnikiem |url=https://www.wisla-plock.pl/pl/steve-kapuadi-trzecim-nowym-zawodnikiem-9170 |publisher=[[Wisła Płock]] |language=pl |date=2 June 2022}}</ref> On 22 August 2023, he moved to another Polish top division side [[Legia Warsaw]].<ref name="Legia">{{Cite web |date=2023-08-22 |title=Steve Kapuadi piłkarzem Legii Warszawa |url=https://legia.com/undefined/pilka-nozna/steve-kapuadi-pilkarzem-legii-warszawa/18473 |access-date=2023-08-22 |website=Legia Warszawa - Strona oficjalna |language=pl-PL}}</ref>

On 25 February 2026, Kapuadi moved to league rivals [[Widzew Łódź]] on a deal until 2030, for a reported fee of €2 million plus €1 million in potential add-ons - the highest ever fee paid between two Polish clubs.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kamieniecki |first1=Piotr |title=Steve Kapuadi odszedł z Legii Warszawa. Hit transferowy Widzewa Łódź stał się faktem |url=https://sport.tvp.pl/91761656/steve-kapuadi-pilkarzem-widzewa-lodz-transfer-z-legii-warszawa-stal-sie-faktem |website=sport.tvp.pl |access-date=27 February 2026 |language=pl |date=25 February 2026}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Włodarczyk |first1=Tomasz |title=Tyle Widzew zapłaci Legii za Kapuadiego. Nowe informacje [NASZ NEWS] |url=https://www.meczyki.pl/newsy/pilka-nozna/tyle-widzew-zaplaci-legii-za-kapuadiego-nowe-informacje-nasz-news/295292 |website=meczyki.pl |access-date=27 February 2026 |language=pl |date=25 February 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
Kapuadi was born in France and is of Congolese descent.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kamieniecki |first1=Piotr |title=Steve Kapuadi coraz bliżej występu w reprezentacji! Piłkarz Legii Warszawa spełni swój cel? |url=https://sport.tvp.pl/85281774/steve-kapuadi-zagra-w-reprezentacji-konga-pilkarz-legii-warszawa-moze-otrzymac-powolanie |website=sport.tvp.pl |access-date=9 May 2025 |language=pl |date=26 February 2025}}</ref>

On 8 May 2025, Kapuadi received his first call-up to the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo national team]] for friendlies against [[Mali national football team|Mali]] and [[Madagascar national football team|Madagascar]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Steve Kapuadi i Afimico Pululu w kadrze Demokratycznej Republiki Konga |url=http://www.90minut.pl/news/337/news3371971-Steve-Kapuadi-i-Afimico-Pululu-w-kadrze-Demokratycznej-Republiki-Konga.html |website=90minut.pl |access-date=9 May 2025 |language=pl |date=8 May 2025}}</ref> He made his international debut against the latter in a 3–1 win on 8 June.<ref>{{cite web |title=Steve Kapuadi zagrał w reprezentacji Demokratycznej Republiki Konga |url=http://www.90minut.pl/news/337/news3376148-Steve-Kapuadi-zagral-w-reprezentacji-Demokratycznej-Republiki-Konga.html |website=90minut.pl |access-date=8 June 2025 |language=pl |date=8 June 2025}}</ref>

